org.gvsig.gpe.xml.stream
Class EventType

java.lang.Object
  org.gvsig.gpe.xml.stream.EventType

public final class EventType
extends java.lang.Object

The EventType enum defines the possible parse events a IXmlStreamReader may return during each call to next().

These are high level events and may not map one to one to the low level Binary XML format tokens. This is so to better reflect the problem domain for this high level API, letting the low level treatment of specific bxml tokens to the implementation criteria.

In general lines, it could be said that the following EventType to TokenType mappings are defined:

EventType TokenType
NONE Header
START_DOCUMENT XmlDeclaration, if present, forced otherwise in order to always return a START_DOCUMENT event
END_DOCUMENT Trailer
START_ELEMENT EmptyElement, EmptyAttrElement, ContentElement, ContentAttrElement
END_ELEMENT ElementEnd, or forced when EmptyElement or EmptyAttrElement
ATTRIBUTE AttributeStart, only used for writing
ATTRIBUTES_END AttributeListEnd, only used for writing
COMMENT Comment
SPACE WhiteSpace
VALUE_STRING, VALUE_BOOL, VALUE_BYTE, VALUE_INT, VALUE_LONG, VALUE_FLOAT, VALUE_DOUBLE CharContent token, followed by the specific value type

Constant Field Values

START_DOCUMENT

public static final EventType START_DOCUMENT
Indicates the parser is positioned at the start of the document. The next call to IXmlStreamReader.next() shall return either START_ELEMENT, COMMENT or END_DOCUMENT if the document is empty.

Constant Field Values

END_ELEMENT

public static final EventType END_ELEMENT
Signals the end of the current element. No content elements such as <element/> and <element att="attval"/> will be notified by an START_ELEMENT and END_ELEMENT event with no value event in between, to preserve semantic equivalence with the <element></element> tag sequence.

Constant Field Values

VALUE_INT

public static final EventType VALUE_INT
Content event that indicates the parser is at a value token whose content is either a Java integer or an array of integers. For the sake of simplicity, the low level SmallNum, Short, UShort, and Int value types are mapped to this event type.

Constant Field Values

VALUE_STRING

public static final EventType VALUE_STRING
Content event that indicates the parser is at a value token whose content is a Java String. There are no such a structure as an array of Strings in the BXML spec.

VALUE_CDATA_CODE

public static final int VALUE_CDATA_CODE
See Also:
Constant Field Values

VALUE_CDATA

public static final EventType VALUE_CDATA
This is event equivalent to the "<![CDATA[content]]>" structure in textual XML, signaled by the CDataSectionToken. This token is essentially equivalent to the CharContentToken, except that its use may be regarded as a hint to a translator to regenerate a CDATA section in textual XML.

Convenience method that returns whether this EventType represents a value token
